894
00:54:26,930 --> 00:54:29,694
- John Tanner, from Tennessee.
- Very nice to meet you.

895
00:54:29,866 --> 00:54:32,266
- What y'all doing?
- I'm here with Corporal Henderson.

896
00:54:32,436 --> 00:54:35,894
- United States Marine Corps.
- Corporal, I was in the Navy.

897
00:54:36,073 --> 00:54:38,564
- 1968 to '72.
- Okay.

898
00:54:38,742 --> 00:54:40,334
We had Marines guarding the base.

899
00:54:40,510 --> 00:54:41,772
- You have kids?
- Yeah.

900
00:54:41,945 --> 00:54:44,106
Is there any way we can
get them to enlist...

901
00:54:44,281 --> 00:54:46,681
...and go over there
and help out with the effort?

902
00:54:46,850 --> 00:54:49,978
- I've got all the brochures.
- One of them has got two children.

903
00:54:51,655 --> 00:54:54,590
See, there's not many congressmen
that have kids over there.

904
00:54:54,758 --> 00:54:56,988
In fact, only one. You know.

905
00:54:57,160 --> 00:54:59,492
So we just thought maybe they...

906
00:54:59,663 --> 00:55:02,097
- You guys should send your kids first.
- That's right.

907
00:55:02,266 --> 00:55:04,564
- What do you think about that?
- I don't disagree.

908
00:55:04,735 --> 00:55:07,329
You don't? Oh, good.
Well, take some brochures.

909
00:55:07,504 --> 00:55:09,529
- At least take a Marine brochure.
- Thank you.

910
00:55:09,706 --> 00:55:11,333
- Pass it around.
- Yeah, well...

911
00:55:11,508 --> 00:55:15,171
Encourage the fellow members
if they're for the war to get behind it.

912
00:55:15,345 --> 00:55:16,778
- Send their own.
- Thank you.

913
00:55:16,947 --> 00:55:19,245
Thank you, sir.
Thank you very much.

914
00:55:20,450 --> 00:55:22,941
Congressman? Michael Moore.

915
00:55:23,120 --> 00:55:24,553
- How you doing today?
- Good.

916
00:55:24,721 --> 00:55:28,452
I'm trying to get members of Congress
to get their kids to enlist in the Army...

917
00:55:28,625 --> 00:55:30,820
...and go over to Iraq.

918
00:55:31,662 --> 00:55:33,061
Congressman.

919
00:55:33,230 --> 00:55:34,663
Congressman.

920
00:55:34,831 --> 00:55:37,061
Congressman Castle?
Congressman Castle?

921
00:55:37,234 --> 00:55:39,464
Congressman. Congressman.

922
00:55:39,636 --> 00:55:41,797
Congressman Doolittle,
Michael Moore.

923
00:55:41,972 --> 00:55:43,667
I was wondering if...

924
00:55:46,810 --> 00:55:48,539
Is there any way to?

925
00:55:51,181 --> 00:55:53,308
Of course, not a single member
of Congress...

926
00:55:53,483 --> 00:55:56,850
...wanted to sacrifice their child
for the war in Iraq.

927
00:55:57,454 --> 00:55:59,319
And who could blame them?

928
00:55:59,489 --> 00:56:01,855
Who would wanna give up
their child?

929
00:56:02,025 --> 00:56:03,925
Would you?

930
00:56:04,094 --> 00:56:05,857
Would he?

931
00:56:07,698 --> 00:56:09,825
I've always been amazed
that the very people...

932
00:56:10,000 --> 00:56:12,161
...forced to live in the worst
parts of town...

933
00:56:12,703 --> 00:56:15,968
...go to the worst schools
and who have it the hardest...

934
00:56:16,139 --> 00:56:21,076
...are always the first to step up
to defend that very system.

935
00:56:21,244 --> 00:56:24,873
They serve so that
we don't have to.

936
00:56:25,048 --> 00:56:29,951
They offer to give up their lives
so that we can be free.

937
00:56:30,120 --> 00:56:34,113
It is remarkable, their gift to us.

938
00:56:34,291 --> 00:56:37,124
And all they ask for in return...

939
00:56:37,294 --> 00:56:40,058
...is that we never send them
into harm's way...

940
00:56:40,597 --> 00:56:43,998
...unless it's absolutely necessary.

941
00:56:45,469 --> 00:56:48,870
Will they ever trust us again?

942
00:56:49,039 --> 00:56:51,234
He had used weapons.

943
00:56:51,408 --> 00:56:52,636
We know where they are.

944
00:56:54,578 --> 00:56:57,103
Around Tikrit, Baghdad
and east, west, south and north.

945
00:56:57,280 --> 00:57:01,580
There is a tie between Iraq
and what happened on 9/11.

946
00:57:01,752 --> 00:57:03,777
The struggle can only end...

947
00:57:03,954 --> 00:57:06,821
...with their complete
and permanent destruction.

948
00:57:06,990 --> 00:57:10,756
We wage a war to save
civilization itself.

949
00:57:12,095 --> 00:57:14,154
We did not seek it.

950
00:57:14,898 --> 00:57:18,629
But we will fight it,
and we will prevail.

951
00:57:18,802 --> 00:57:20,827
George Orwell once wrote...

952
00:57:21,004 --> 00:57:25,771
...that, "It's not a matter of whether
